<html>
	<head>
		<title>Indention Page</title>
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Language" content="en-us">
		<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=windows-1252">
	</head>
	<body>
		<p><IMG alt="" src="Indention.jpg"></p>
		<p>This is the Indention page of the Brainchild configuration program. With it you can 
			change several indention settings and options of the Brainchild control. The 
			various settings are explaned below:</p>
		<table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellPadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Automatic indention</td>
				<td width="65%">When this option is turned on the brainchild control will automatically 
					place the caret on the same column position as the first character on the line 
					when you press the return or enter key.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Smart indention</td>
				<td width="65%">This option is only available when automatic indention is turned on. 
					The smart indention option allows you to define text fragments which will 
					indent the caret one tab stop to the left or right. For example in the image 
					above you see some examples for the C language.
					<p>When you enter the line:</p>
					<pre>	return ( bValue );</pre>
					<p>and you press the return key the caret is automatically placed one tab stop left of 
						where the return statement is placed.</p>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Tab size</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you can set the maximum number of spaces a tab stop is. The value 
					entered here must be between 2 and 24.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Smart indention entries</td>
				<td width="65%">Here you see the smart indention text fragments listed. You can also 
					see a small toolbar with four buttons, <IMG alt="" src="NewTB.gif">, <IMG alt="" src="DelTB.gif">,&nbsp;<IMG alt="" src="UpTB.gif">
					and <IMG alt="" src="DownTB.gif">.
					<p>With the&nbsp;<IMG alt="" src="NewTB.gif"> button you add a new entry to the list. 
						With the&nbsp;<IMG alt="" src="DelTB.gif"> button you delete the currently 
						selected entrye. With the&nbsp;<IMG alt="" src="UpTB.gif"> and&nbsp;<IMG alt="" src="DownTB.gif">
						buttons you can move the currently selected entry up or down in the list.</p>
				</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Edit control</td>
				<td width="65%">This edit control allows you to change the text from the curretly 
					selected entry.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td width="35%">Indent left/right</td>
				<td width="65%">With these radio buttons you determine wether the selected entry will 
					indent the caret left or right.</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</body>
</html>
